.:: Puzzle 2x6-Level-7-7::.
6 different games are played: billiard, scrabble, bridge, poker, domino, whist
The people use 6 different means of transport: car, motorbike, quad-bike, scooter, ship, trike
 1. the person playing poker is somewhere to the right of the person driving the car##5
 2. the person playing scrabble is not the person driving the quad-bike##6
 3. the person playing billiard is the person driving the ship##1
 4. the person playing whist is not the person driving the quad-bike##6
 5. the person playing scrabble is somewhere to the right of the person playing bridge##5
 6. the person playing bridge is on the left of the person playing whist##1
 7. the person driving the quad-bike is on the right of the person playing scrabble##1
 8. the person playing poker is somewhere to the right of the person driving the scooter##5
 9. the person driving the trike is in an even position##4
10. the person playing domino is in an odd position##4
11. the person playing whist is somewhere to the left of the person driving the scooter##5
12. the person driving the motorbike is on the left of the person driving the car##1
13. the person playing poker is on the left or right of the person playing billiard##3
14. the person driving the trike is somewhere between the person playing poker and the person playing whist##7

.:: Answer ::.
|             |     1     |      2       |       3        |    4     |        5        |    6     |
| Game         | bridge    | whist | domino | scrabble | poker | billiard |
| Transport   | motorbike | car          | scooter        | trike    | quad-bike       | ship     |

